Yola â€” Two separate accidents on Ngurore-Mayo-Belwa Highway have claimed 13 lives and 21 others seriously wounded. The first accident occurred on Monday night while the second took place the same on the particular road. The information officer of Mayo-Belwa local government area, Mr. Kabiru Kelly, said that six lives were lost in the mishap and three others sustained life-threatening injuries. Kelly said that the first accident which involved a Sharon bus occurred when the driver attempted to avoid a pothole, lost control and rammed into a pole. He said that the victims were taken to Yola Specialist Hospital in Adamawa State while the injured were receiving treatment at the Mayo-Belwa cottage hospital. According to Kelly, the second accident was through a head-on-collision between a Hummer bus and a Toyota Starlet car. Kelly explained that the accident was caused when the driver of the bus tried to overtake a heavy duty vehicle and rammed into the oncoming Starlet car. A whole family including a father, his wife and their four children who were on their way from Jalingo in Taraba State to Zamfara State were involved in the second accident. The bodies of the dead and the injured were taken to Mayo-Belwa General Hospital, Kelly said.